step.reason:
\text{If } X = [x_{ij}]_{\,m\times n} \text{ and k is a scalar then,}\\
\text{kX is another matrix of order m\times n}\\
\text{such that }
kX = [k(x_{ij})]_{\,m\times n}

X_{m \times n} + Y_{m \times n} = S_{m \times n} = [s_{ij}]_{m \times n}\text{ where,}\\
s_{ij} = a_{ij} + b_{ij} \, (\forall \text{ possible ij values)}. \text{ So, corresponding}\\
\text{elements are added to form the }\textbf{resultant matrix.}
